This system will require the operator to load the filler tube into a holding fixture with the brackets loosely installed. The brackets and filler tube will be nested with profile shaped blocks and locating pins. Once the operator completes the load and all required conditions are met, a two hand cycle start is required to be depressed. The TOX air over system will then initiate and create the required joint. After cycle is complete the tube will unclamp and allow the operator to remove the completed assembly.) PER EST #21405MNV

ITEMS NAME:  CONVERSION OF DEDICATED D2XX TOX MACHINE
PRODUCTION ASSEMBLY PART #84105765 (D2XX W/GAS CAP)
ACCOUNT #6360-15
PROJECT #MIS-01  PER EST #22573MNV
MACHINE, Test station for Top Chord Clinching machine. Test station will consist of a single station C-frame with 2 Tox cylinders and  1 intensifier unit, a center mandrel section to hold the die buttons and to strip the part off of the mandrel after clinching. Two Linear rails and 4 bearing blocks mounted to a small fabricated test frame will simulate the final machine frame construction, thus allowing a comprehensive review of any potential failure modes. A mock controll unit with a PLC to control the test station and cylce it for a pre-determined number of cycles, to be determined later, is also included. After the number of pre-determined cycles has been acheived the test station will be disassembled and all of the components will be checked for wear and failure points. If the test station is successful and RBI Solar decides to proceed with the order the cost of the mechanical components, labor and the Tox equipment will be deducted from the total price of the clinching machine. The electrical portion of the test station will not be deducted from the total price of the machine as the components will not be used in the final product. If the test station fails Wilmington Precision and RBI Solar will discuss the next course of action and determine whether to re-design and modify the current test station, all charges associated for this will be billed accordingly, or to use the Tox Pressotechnik designed C-Frame and center mandrel components.  PER EST #23414RBI   Note: RBI Solar will need to provide sample c-channel parts to conduct the testing with.   Note: This quote includes all necessary safety equipment. RBI will only need to provide air and power to the test station for operation.   Note: The amount reflected on this quote, $45,500.00, will be credited towards the final machine price if the test station works.

MIDDLE BRACKET TOX FIXTURE #NV71B7490   Quick change fixturing to adapt C1 Tox machine to the C1TL tube configuration. This is for the middle and lower bracket. The lower bracket will use the existing fixturing from the C1UG and C1UL tube configuration with slight modifications. Fixture to consist of new center nest for middle bracket, quick change base plates with angle risers and SMC swing arm clamps with all necessary part locators to orient the part in the Tox machine for the middle bracket. The lower bracket will need a new quick change base plate and a new angle riser. This quote does not include new Tox tools; punch and die. It also does not include any installation or de-bug at your facility. WPM reserves the right to modify this quote after the final design to account for additional components needed to orient the lower bracket in the machine. This system will require the operator to load the filler tube into a holding fixture with the brackets loosely installed. The brackets and filler tube will be nested with profile shaped blocks and locating pins. Once the operator completes the load and all required conditions are met, a two hand cycle start is required to be depressed. The TOX air over system will then initiate and create the required joint. After cycle is complete the tube will unclamp and allow the operator to remove the completed assembly.) PER EST #21405MNV
